'''See No Evil''' is an anomalous level of The Backrooms.
<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Courier New; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #d9d9d9, 0em 0em 1.0em black;


 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ffffff, #ebebeb);

             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;">Description</span>{{Underline|c7c7c7}} </center>

{{Blurimage|file=stopstaring.jpg|caption=Come and see.}}
Due to the properties of '''See No Evil''', only the initial entry area has been successfully photographed and visually documented. The entry area appears as a small guest bedroom furnished with old-fashioned furniture and early 2010s architecture. The walls are pale white and undecorated, with the exception of a single symbol of a triangle containing three intersecting circles engraved into the wall above the bed and a hanging grandfather clock mounted beside the room's only door. The room is illuminated by a soft, desaturated light entering through a window adjacent to the bed. Behind the window, no outside is visible and only pure whiteness can be observed.

The bed is pushed tightly into the left corner of the room. Its frame is constructed from dark, polished wood and features carved detailing, rounded edges, and a slatted headboard. The bedding is neatly arranged and covered with white fabric patterned with faded floral designs in gray-blue and gray-pink hues. The ceiling is bare, containing only a single exposed light bulb suspended from a cord. The floor consists of patterned wooden tiles partially covered by a long ornamental rug displaying circular and floral motifs in beige, brown, and faded red. In the other corner of the room is an old-fashioned wooden dresser fitted with rounded handles and covered by a lace cloth. A single chair is positioned beside it.

The remainder of '''See No Evil''' appears to comprise a residential structure approximately equal in size to an average family home. Survivor accounts indicate that the architecture and furnishing style remain consistent throughout the level, however, those observations have only been made via physical touch. Each documented entry has presented a different internal layout, but the overall dimensions of the structure appeared unchanged.

No documented case exists of two wanderers encountering one another within the level.

<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Courier New; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #d9d9d9, 0em 0em 1.0em black;


 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ffffff, #ebebeb);

             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;"> Properties</span>{{Underline|c7c7c7}} </center>
Upon entering '''See No Evil''', individuals are advised to immediately close their eyes and refrain from reopening them until they have confirmed their exit from the level. Blindfolding oneself is strongly recommended.

<div style="
    border-left: 2px solid #ffffff;
    padding-left: 30px;
    margin: 20px 0;
    font-family: Courier New;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: bold;
">
It will do anything to make you break. It may sound like your closest loved relatives. It may sound like your wife. It may sound like your pets. It may sound like your best friend. It's not what it'll make you believe it is. Do not open your eyes.
</div>

Shortly after entry, one will begin to hear their family members, friends, or other emotionally significant individuals. The source of these sounds and the exact nature of the visual anomaly present within '''See No Evil''' remains unknown, as all cases involving direct visual exposure have resulted in severe psychological collapse. Wanderers who viewed it entered states of extreme shock, panic, and mental instability, ultimately ending their own lives shortly afterward, frequently utilizing nearby objects or personal equipment.

Individuals who have successfully exited the level consistently exhibit symptoms of severe psychological trauma, including prolonged shock responses, anxiety, and recurring distress associated with the auditory phenomena experienced within the level. Examples of things that one could hear while within the level include, but are not limited to:

*Family members undergoing severe torture

*A close relative mutilating themselves

*Terrified children being physically abused or slowly murdered

*Deceased loved ones pleading for help

*Sounds of [[The Frontrooms]]

*A rescure team

*A dying best friend

*One's pets being skinned or beaten

*One themselves committing acts of brutal violence against loved ones

*A romantic partner using seduction

*A doctor informing one they were in a coma and must open their eyes to fully awaken

*One's younger self reliving traumatic experiences

*Other

Periods of sudden complete silence may occasionally occur within the level. These intervals should not be interpreted as indications of safety or successful progression.

<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Courier New; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #d9d9d9, 0em 0em 1.0em black;


 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ffffff, #ebebeb);

             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;">Entities</span>{{Underline|c7c7c7}} </center>

No entities have been confirmed due to the strict "eyes-closed" survival protocol. Whether the source of the auditory phenomena and visual anomaly constitutes a single entity, multiple entities, or an inherent property of the level itself remains unknown.

<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Courier New; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #d9d9d9, 0em 0em 1.0em black;


 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ffffff, #ebebeb);

