             animation: gradient 5s infinite;">Colonies & Outposts</span>{{Underline|c7c7c7}} </center>

None exist within the level due to its nature.

<center>
<span style="font-size:25px; font-family:Courier New; text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em #d9d9d9, 0em 0em 1.0em black;


 background: linear-gradient(90deg, #ffffff, #ebebeb);

             background-size: 400%; 
             -webkit-background-clip: text;
             -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
             animation: gradient 5s infinite;">Entrances and Exits</span>{{Underline|c7c7c7}} </center>

===Entrances===
The method of entry into '''See No Evil''' has not been conclusively determined. Due to the rarity of the level, the low survival rate associated with it, and the severe psychological condition of those who have exited it, reliable information remains limited. Current speculation suggests that the level may be accessed by noclipping through damaged or broken mirrors, particularly when the mirror emits sounds resembling distant ambience of [[The Frontrooms]] or barely audiable voices calling for help.
===Exits===
According to the limited number of survivor accounts, the only known method of exiting the level is to navigate the structure without visual perception, locate the house's front entrance, and leave through it. Upon crossing the threshold, all auditory phenomena cease. When the individual opens their eyes, they will find themselves in a random [https://backrooms.fandom.com/wiki/Category:Safe Safe Level] set in an outdoor environment, with no trace of the house behind them.

Survivors consistently report that the front entrance is distinguished by being the only closed door within the level. All other doors encountered throughout the structure remain open or partially open and do not serve as exits.

Wanderers are strongly advised not to reopen their eyes solely because the auditory phenomena have ceased. As mentioned earlier, silence alone does not confirm successful escape. Unless the individual has consciously operated a doorknob and passed through a previously closed door, they should assume they remain within '''See No Evil'''.


